ODE V.

Non yet is thy young heifer broke Το bend her frontlet fair Obedient to the galling yoke, Or drag the cumbrous share; N or may her tender loins endure the weight And rude embraces of her ardent mate.

The grassy mend is her delight, Where gelid fountains burst

Forth from some roek’s impending height Το slake her raging thirst3

Among the osiers now she loves to stray, And sport with frisking calves the livelong day.

Oh, pluch not thou in early spring . The grape all green and sour, When glowing Antumn soon shall bring His purple-tinted store; And many a ripened cluster heaped on high shall tempt thine appetite and charm thine eye.
